#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:78
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:68
#: patterns/faq/default.php:66
#: patterns/page/home.php:1716
msgid "Menus are now managed via the Navigation Block. Click on the header area inside the Site Editor to add, remove, or reorder links directly on the canvas without leaving the design view."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:85
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:97
#: patterns/faq/default.php:73
#: patterns/page/home.php:1748
msgid "How can I add animations to blocks?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:87
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:99
#: patterns/faq/default.php:75
#: patterns/page/home.php:1750
msgid "Motion parameters are integrated directly into the block's settings panel. Within the Animation control group, you can define kinetic properties including the triggering Event (such as \"Enter\"), the Effect style, Easing curve, and precise timing curves for Duration and Delay without writing any code."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:94
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:106
#: patterns/faq/default.php:82
#: patterns/page/home.php:1758
msgid "How do I create an FAQ accordion?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:96
#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:108
#: patterns/faq/default.php:84
#: patterns/page/home.php:1760
msgid "Deploy a pre-configured accordion instantly from the Patterns library, or construct one manually using the native List Block variation. By relying on standard core architecture rather than proprietary blocks, your content retains absolute portability across any future environment."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:103
#: patterns/faq/default.php:95
#: patterns/page/home.php:1772
msgid "How can I display blog posts on the home page?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:105
#: patterns/faq/default.php:97
#: patterns/page/home.php:1774
msgid "Inject dynamic content instantly by dragging a layout from the Blog Patterns library onto your canvas. Control the data stream using the Query Loop block, allowing you to filter categories and define display parameters with granular precision."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:112
#: patterns/faq/default.php:104
#: patterns/page/home.php:1782
msgid "What is the difference between Templates and Pages?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:114
#: patterns/faq/default.php:106
#: patterns/page/home.php:1784
msgid "Pages hold your specific content (like \"About Us\"). Templates define the structure wrapping that content (like headers, sidebars, and footers). Editing a Template affects all Pages that use it."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:121
#: patterns/faq/default.php:167
#: patterns/page/home.php:1852
msgid "Does this theme require any plugins?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion-wide.php:123
#: patterns/faq/default.php:169
#: patterns/page/home.php:1854
msgid "No. We operate on a strict zero-dependency architecture. Every layout, pattern, and utility is native to the framework, ensuring you never rely on external software to achieve core functionality."
msgstr ""

