#: patterns/page/home.php:1724
msgid "How do I change fonts and colors globally?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:77
#: patterns/page/home.php:1726
msgid "Open the Styles panel (the half-shaded circle icon) in the top-right of the Editor. Changes made here propagate instantly across the entire site architecture, updating all blocks simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:84
#: patterns/page/home.php:1734
msgid "How do I add custom SVG images?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:86
#: patterns/page/home.php:1736
msgid "Use the Icon Block to manage curated sets or the Inline SVG variation to paste raw XML code directly onto the canvas."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/accordion.php:90
msgid "The theme allows secure SVG uploads to the Media Library by default, with built-in sanitization — no additional plugin required."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:113
#: patterns/page/home.php:1792
msgid "How do I edit the Header or Footer?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:115
#: patterns/page/home.php:1794
msgid "These are Template Parts. You can edit them contextually while viewing any template in the Editor, or manage them specifically under Appearance → Editor → Patterns."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:122
#: patterns/page/home.php:1802
msgid "Where do I find the pre-made layouts?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:124
#: patterns/page/home.php:1804
msgid "Open the Block Inserter (+) and switch to the Patterns tab. Here you can browse categorized sections (Headers, Grids, Call to Actions) and drag them directly onto your canvas."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:131
#: patterns/page/home.php:1812
msgid "Where do I add custom CSS?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:133
#: patterns/page/home.php:1814
msgid "Open the Styles panel, click the three dots menu, and select Additional CSS. This allows you to inject code that applies strictly to the framework's root without external plugins."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:140
#: patterns/page/home.php:1822
msgid "How do I set a different template for a specific page?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:142
#: patterns/page/home.php:1824
msgid "Inside the page editor, look for the Template setting in the right sidebar (Page tab). Click the template name to swap it (e.g., from \"Default\" to \"Blank Canvas\") or create a new custom one."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:149
#: patterns/page/home.php:1832
msgid "How do I revert changes if I break a template?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:151
#: patterns/page/home.php:1834
msgid "If a template is modified, a blue dot appears next to it in the Site Editor. Click the three dots next to the template name and select Clear Customizations to reset it to the theme's native default."
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:158
#: patterns/page/home.php:1842
msgid "How can I save user dark mode preferences?"
msgstr ""

#: patterns/faq/default.php:160
#: patterns/page/home.php:1844
msgid "The system defaults to the visitor's OS setting (prefers-color-scheme) automatically. However, if the manual toggle is engaged, a local cookie is initialized to persist the user's specific override across sessions."
msgstr ""

